text: was a town located in Jōbō District, Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 8,188 and a density of 64.18 persons per km². The total area was 127.58 km². On October 1, 2004, Kayō, along with the town of Kamogawa (from Mitsu District), was merged to create the town of Kibichūō (in the newly created Kaga District). Category:Dissolved municipalities of Okayama Prefecture
title: Kayō, Okayama
